Patterns in the Juan Fernandez fur seal faecal microbiome: R script 2

Constanza Toro

This is script number 2 of a series of html files containing all the code used for the statistical analysis of "Patterns in the Juan Fernandez fur seal (Arctophoca philippii philippii) faecal microbiome". The direct outputs of this analysis were the object generated with Script 1 located in the R_code folder within this GitHub repository. This script aims to look at differences in three alpha diversity estimators (Chao 1, Shannon-Weiner and Simpson) between the locations from which samples were collected.

This script includes the full alpha diversity analysis:
Note: files needed to run this coded were generated in section 3 of Script 1

1.1. Full data

  • Load libraries
library(rstatix)
library(tidyverse)
library(DescTools)
  • Load metadata
    Note: using non-normalised data
# Full meta
read.csv("F2meta.csv") -> JFFS.meta

JFFS.meta$Year <- as.factor(JFFS.meta$Year)

# Core meta
read.csv("F2coremeta.csv") -> coremeta

coremeta$Year <- as.factor(coremeta$Year)
  • Data clean-up Locations with only one sample will be removed from this analysis
# Full meta
JFFS.meta %>%
  filter(Location != "vaqueria", 
         Location != "piedra_carvajal", 
         Location != "pta_trueno") -> JFFS.metaF

# Core meta
coremeta %>%
  filter(Location != "vaqueria", 
         Location != "piedra_carvajal", 
         Location != "pta_trueno") -> coremetaF

#boxplot for the three indexes

  geom_jitter(height = 0,
              size = 1,
              width = 0.2) +
    facet_wrap(~ index, 
               ncol = 3, 
               scales = "free") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_blank(),
        axis.ticks = element_blank(),
        axis.title.x = element_blank(),
        axis.title.y = element_blank(),
        panel.border = element_rect(colour = "grey", 
                                    fill=NA),
        panel.background = element_blank(),
        legend.title = element_text(size = 12),
        legend.text = element_text(size = 10)) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") +
  scale_colour_brewer(palette = "Set1") +
  labs(title = "Comparison of three different alpha diversity indices",
       subtitle = "Filtered non-rarefied dataset")

For all three indices there was a consistent trend where samples collected from Tierras Blancas showed higher alpha diversity than the other three locations. This trend was also observed when using the core dataset. However, the differences in sample sizes as well as low sample numbers may have contributed to the lack of statistical significance in the many of the comparisons. The difference was more consistent with Shannon and Simpson. Both indices take in to account the relative abundance of each ASV. Location only explained a very small percentage of the alpha diversity variability.
